710610f-a.text:
Eleventh Avenue, west side, north from 24th Street, showing
Baltimore and Ohio Storage Warehouses.
P. L. Sperr  March 3, 1929

711788f-b.text:
W. 24th Street, east from a point to the west of Eleventh Avenue (in No. 1; 2&3 being from and across the Avenue). Note the cleared areas at the S.W. and N.E. corners. Upon the first of these sites stood the old car house of the New York Railway Co. and is seen only in No. 1 and upon the latter a lumber yard and a 2 story structure bearing No. 202-8 Eleventh Avenue. The dining car seen is at the S.E. corner and replaces a former tenement (no. 200).

April 3, 1937.
Views 1,2 and 3

P.L. Sperr
